<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u><span lang="EN-GB">International
Week at ISM, 24<sup>th</sup> -28<sup>th</sup> October 2011</span></u></b><u><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p></o:p></span></u></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">Dear Parents,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">It’s time to celebrate the rich cultural
diversity of our school community. At ISM we are extremely proud of the
international nature of our school. To celebrate this and to develop a wider
understanding of the global community within which our students live and learn,
we are planning an International week at school. In recognition of this we are
extending it from a day to become an International Week of celebrations.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u><span lang="EN-GB">For
Years 1-3<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">This year during the International week each
class will focus on a country (not from our student community) and learn in
depth about these following countries. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span lang="EN-GB">1A</span></b><span lang="EN-GB">- Canada<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">1F</b>- Mongolia<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">1M</b>-
Thailand<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span lang="EN-GB">2C-</span></b><span lang="EN-GB"> Vietnam<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">2D</b>- Qatar<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span lang="EN-GB">3C-</span></b><span lang="EN-GB"> Jamaica<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal">3D</b>- Madagascar <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal">3S</b>- Peru<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">Your support in helping with information,
books, souvenirs, music, costumes, pamphlets, food and/or flags for <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u>any</u></b> of the above mentioned
countries would be much appreciated and welcomed by all. It will make the
teaching and learning meaningful and fun!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">The week will begin with a quiz on Monday
and the celebration of our cultural diversity will continue with an assembly
with international music and multi cultural games (for students only) on
Friday.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u><span lang="EN-GB"><span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp;</span>Friday-28<sup>th</sup> October: Dress up day-
National costumes, flag colours<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p><span style="text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span lang="EN-GB">All parents of Lower school (Foundation
stage and Y1 to 3) are invited to school on Friday 28<sup>th</sup> October at
8.30 – 10.00 am.</span></u><span lang="EN-GB"> On this day you and your children are
welcome to come to school dressed in your national costume/flag colours/ football
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">t-shirts. Also please bring a plate of a national
dish to share with other children and parents in the class. This would give
everyone a true taste of being part of an international community. You will be
able to participate with your child in completing an activity set out by the
teacher and then to sample some of the food.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><span lang="EN-GB">Foundation
stage </span></b><span lang="EN-GB">will continue the celebrations by focussing
on different countries for the rest of the day. Please contact your child’s
teacher if you would like to help.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">School will finish as normal at 3.20pm.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">Looking forward to seeing you all at school
on Friday the 28<sup>th</sup> Of October.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">We are very grateful for your continued
support.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-GB">Thank you,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

